# When performing an action which has a dependency on a tool or file or any content, never assume anything about it.

Never assume it is NOT installed or does not exist.

Never assume that it IS installed or does not exist.

Always issue the relative command, search or required "check procees" to DETERMINE the actual state before proceeding with actions or changes or troubleshooting.

Never assume how something is configured.  Search for and view the associated configuration file(s)/setting(s).
